%% Each adapter takes a closure (strategy) and wraps the previous
%% iterator. The whole pipeline is lazy until a consumer pulls.
flowchart LR
    Src[0..u64] --> M[".map(|n| n * n)"]
    M --> F[".filter(|&sq| sq % 2 == 0)"]
    F --> T[".take_while(|&sq| sq &lt; 1000)"]
    T --> C{consumer}
    C -->|.sum::&lt;u64&gt;()| Sum[u64]
    C -->|.collect()| Vec[Vec&lt;u64&gt;]
    C -->|.find(pred)| Opt[Option&lt;u64&gt;]

    note1["map's strategy: the mapping fn<br/>filter's strategy: the predicate<br/>take_while's strategy: the stop predicate<br/>each closure is a one-line Strategy"]
    T -.-> note1
